Defendant Alexander Raymond Jones in court.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that this is a motion to terminate the DPA based on the defendant submitted to a positive test.  Court questions the defendant regarding counsel.  Defendant would like to continue today without an Attorney.    Court finds waiver of Attorney made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.   Court questions the defendant regarding the motion.
Defendant agrees with the motion to terminate.
BY THE COURT:  Court grants the motion to terminate; finds the defendant guilty and enters the Judgment of Conviction as of today's date.

Defendant would like to proceed with sentencing.
Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations.

BY THE COURT:  Pay and costs = $442.00
  DNA Sample + $200.00 Surcharge
  Defendant agrees to the $15.00 payment plan fee.
Payment Plan:  $50.00/month commencing on April 1, 2017
Motion hearing on February 16, 2017 at 11:30 am.
in Support to Motion to Terminate Deferred Prosecution Agreement

Defendant Alexander Raymond Jones in court.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that an offer was provided at a pre-trial conference and there is resolution today.    Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Upon the defendant's plea and prior to adjudication, defendant will enter into a Deferred Prosecution Agreement for a period of:  12 months with conditions.
Defendant agrees.    Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.    Defendant waives their right to an attorney.    Court finds waiver of Attorney made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.
Defendant enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  

BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea; approves and signs the 12 month DPA with conditions.

Pre-trial conference on June 21, 2016 at 10:00 am.
Return date on July 21, 2016 at 03:30 pm.

Defendant Alexander Raymond Jones in court.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee states that bond needs to be set along with booking.  Court confirms defendant's address.  Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint & waives it's reading.  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant understands.    Defendant waives their right to an attorney in order to have a conference with the District Attorney.    Court finds waiver made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.
Court finds probable cause to support the charges. 

  BY THE COURT:  Court enters a Not Guilty plea on behalf of the defendant.

  Atty Hendee has no objection to a signature bond with conditions.

  BY THE COURT:  Court sets a $500 Signature bond with conditions:
*Appear for booking today

Court questions the defendant.    Defendant waives their right to an attorney in order to have a conference with the District Attorney.
BY THE COURT:  Set for Return and pre-trial  Return date scheduled for July 21, 2016 at 03:30 pm.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 21, 2016 at 10:00 am.
